name: http_server
comment: HTTP is a configuration for Centrifugo HTTP server.

children.name: address
children.comment: Address to bind HTTP server to.

children.name: port
children.comment: Port to bind HTTP server to.

children.name: internal_address
children.comment:

which are normally should not be exposed to the outside world.

children.name: internal_port

children.comment: TLS configuration for HTTP server.

children.comment: Enabled turns on using TLS.

The server uses this certificate to verify the client's certificate during the TLS handshake.

children.comment: InsecureSkipVerify turns off server certificate verification.

children.comment: ServerName is used to verify the hostname on the returned certificates.

children.comment: TLSAutocert for automatic TLS certificates from ACME provider (ex. Let's Encrypt).

children.name: tls_external

children.name: internal_tls

name: broker
comment:
Broker allows to configure a message broker to use. Broker is responsible for PUB/SUB functionality
and channel message history and idempotency cache.
By default, memory Broker is used. Memory broker is superfast, but it's not distributed and all
data stored in memory (thus lost after node restart). Redis Broker provides seamless horizontal
scalability, fault-tolerance, and persistence over Centrifugo restarts. Centrifugo also supports
Nats Broker which only implements at most once PUB/SUB semantics.

children.name: type
children.comment: Type of broker to use. Can be "memory", "redis", "nats" at this point.

children.name: redis
children.comment: Redis is a configuration for "redis" broker.

children.comment: Nats is a configuration for NATS broker. It does not support history/recovery/cache.

children.name: url

children.name: prefix
children.comment:
Prefix allows customizing channel prefix in Nats to work with a single Nats from different
unrelated Centrifugo setups.

children.name: dial_timeout
children.comment: DialTimeout is a timeout for establishing connection to Nats.

children.name: write_timeout
children.comment: WriteTimeout is a timeout for write operation to Nats.

children.name: tls
children.comment: TLS for the Nats connection. TLS is not used if nil.

children.name: allow_wildcards
children.comment:
AllowWildcards allows to enable wildcard subscriptions. By default, wildcard subscriptions
are not allowed. Using wildcard subscriptions can't be combined with join/leave events and presence
because subscriptions do not belong to a concrete channel after with wildcards, while join/leave events
require concrete channel to be published. And presence does not make a lot of sense for wildcard
subscriptions - there could be subscribers which use different mask, but still receive subset of updates.
It's required to use channels without wildcards to for mentioned features to work properly. When
using wildcard subscriptions a special care is needed regarding security - pay additional
attention to a proper permission management.

children.name: raw_mode
children.comment:
RawMode allows enabling raw communication with Nats. When on, Centrifugo subscribes to channels
without adding any prefixes to channel name. Proper prefixes must be managed by the application in this
case. Data consumed from Nats is sent directly to subscribers without any processing. When publishing
to Nats Centrifugo does not add any prefixes to channel names also. Centrifugo features like Publication
tags, Publication ClientInfo, join/leave events are not supported in raw mode.

children.name: enabled
children.comment: Enabled enables raw mode when true.

children.name: channel_replacements
children.comment:
ChannelReplacements is a map where keys are strings to replace and values are replacements.
For example, you have Centrifugo namespace "chat" and using channel "chat:index", but you want to
use channel "chat.index" in Nats. Then you can define SymbolReplacements map like this: {":": "."}.
In this case Centrifugo will replace all ":" symbols in channel name with "." before sending to Nats.
Broker keeps reverse mapping to the original channel to broadcast to proper channels when processing
messages received from Nats.

children.name: prefix
children.comment:
Prefix is a string that will be added to all channels when publishing messages to Nats, subscribing
to channels in Nats. It's also stripped from channel name when processing messages received from Nats.
By default, no prefix is used.

name: presence_manager
comment:
PresenceManager allows to configure a presence manager to use. Presence manager is responsible for
presence information storage and retrieval. By default, memory PresenceManager is used. Memory
PresenceManager is superfast, but it's not distributed. Redis PresenceManager provides a seamless
horizontal scalability.

children.name: type
children.comment: Type of presence manager to use. Can be "memory" or "redis" at this point.

children.name: token
children.comment:
Token is a configuration for token generation and verification. When enabled, this configuration
is used for both connection and subscription tokens. See also SubscriptionToken to use a separate
configuration for subscription tokens.

children.name: subscription_token
children.comment:
SubscriptionToken is a configuration for subscription token generation and verification. When enabled,
Centrifugo will use this configuration for subscription tokens only. Configuration in Token is then only
used for connection tokens.

children.name: allow_anonymous_connect_without_token
children.comment:
AllowAnonymousConnectWithoutToken allows to connect to Centrifugo without a token. In this case connection will
be accepted but client will be anonymous (i.e. will have empty user ID).

children.name: disallow_anonymous_connection_tokens
children.comment:
DisallowAnonymousConnectionTokens disallows anonymous connection tokens. When enabled, Centrifugo will not
accept connection tokens with empty user ID.

children.name: expired_close_delay
children.comment: ExpiredConnectionCloseDelay is a delay before closing connection after it becomes expired.

children.name: expired_sub_close_delay
children.comment: ExpiredSubCloseDelay is a delay before closing subscription after it becomes expired.

children.name: stale_close_delay
children.comment: StaleConnectionCloseDelay is a delay before closing stale connection (which does not authenticate after connecting).

children.name: channel_limit
children.comment: ChannelLimit is a maximum number of channels client can subscribe to.

children.name: queue_max_size
children.comment: QueueMaxSize is a maximum size of message queue for client connection in bytes.

children.name: presence_update_interval
children.comment: PresenceUpdateInterval is a period of time how often to update presence info for subscriptions of connected client.

children.name: concurrency
children.comment: Concurrency is a maximum number of concurrent operations for client connection. If not set only one operation can be processed at a time.

children.name: channel_position_check_delay
children.comment: ChannelPositionCheckDelay is a delay between channel position checks for client subscriptions.

children.name: channel_position_max_time_lag
children.comment:
ChannelPositionMaxTimeLag is a maximum allowed time lag for publications for subscribers with positioning on. When
exceeded we mark connection with insufficient state. By default, not used - i.e. Centrifugo does not take lag into
account for positioning. See pub_sub_time_lag_seconds as a helpful Prometheus metric.

children.name: connection_limit
children.comment: ConnectionLimit is a maximum number of connections Centrifugo node can accept.

children.name: user_connection_limit
children.comment: UserConnectionLimit is a maximum number of connections Centrifugo node can accept from a single user.

children.name: connection_rate_limit
children.comment: ConnectionRateLimit is a maximum number of connections per second Centrifugo node can accept.

children.name: connect_include_server_time
children.comment: ConnectIncludeServerTime allows to include server time in connect reply of client protocol.

children.name: history_max_publication_limit
children.comment: HistoryMaxPublicationLimit is a maximum number of publications Centrifugo returns in client history requests.

children.name: recovery_max_publication_limit
children.comment: RecoveryMaxPublicationLimit is a maximum number of publications Centrifugo returns during client recovery.

children.name: insecure_skip_token_signature_verify
children.comment: InsecureSkipTokenSignatureVerify allows to skip token signature verification. This can be useful for testing purposes.

children.name: user_id_http_header
children.comment: UserIDHTTPHeader is a name of HTTP header to extract user ID from. If set Centrifugo will try to extract user ID from this header.

children.name: insecure
children.comment: Insecure allows to disable auth features in client protocol. Obviously - must not be used in production until you know what you do.

children.name: subscribe_to_user_personal_channel
children.comment:
SubscribeToUserPersonalChannel is a configuration for a feature to automatically subscribe user to a personal channel
using server-side subscription.

children.name: connect_code_to_unidirectional_disconnect
children.comment:

children.name: enabled

children.name: to

children.name: without_namespace
children.comment:
WithoutNamespace is a configuration of channels options for channels which do not have namespace.
Generally, we recommend always use channel namespaces but this option can be useful for simple setups.

children.name: presence
children.comment:
Presence turns on presence information for channel. Presence has
information about all clients currently subscribed to a channel.

children.name: join_leave
children.comment:
JoinLeave turns on join/leave messages for a channel.
When client subscribes on a channel join message sent to all
subscribers in this channel (including current client). When client
leaves channel (unsubscribes) leave message sent. This option does
not fit well for channels with many subscribers because every
subscribe/unsubscribe event results into join/leave event broadcast
to all other active subscribers thus overloads server with tons of
messages. Use accurately for channels with small number of active
subscribers.

children.name: force_push_join_leave
children.comment: ForcePushJoinLeave forces sending join/leave messages towards subscribers.

children.name: history_size
children.comment:
HistorySize determines max amount of history messages for a channel,
Zero value means no history for channel. Centrifuge history has an
auxiliary role with current Engines – it can not replace your backend
persistent storage.

children.name: history_ttl
children.comment:
HistoryTTL is a time to live for history cache. Server maintains a window of
messages in memory (or in Redis with Redis engine), to prevent infinite memory
grows it's important to remove history for inactive channels.

children.name: history_meta_ttl
children.comment:
HistoryMetaTTL is a time to live for history stream meta information. Must be
much larger than HistoryTTL in common scenario. If zero, then we use global value
set over default_history_meta_ttl on configuration top level.

children.name: force_positioning
children.comment:
ForcePositioning enables client positioning. This means that StreamPosition
will be exposed to the client and server will look that no messages from
PUB/SUB layer lost. In the loss found – client is disconnected (or unsubscribed)
with reconnect (resubscribe) code.

children.name: allow_positioning
children.comment: AllowPositioning allows positioning when client asks about it.

children.name: force_recovery
children.comment:
ForceRecovery enables recovery mechanism for channels. This means that
server will try to recover missed messages for resubscribing client.
This option uses publications from history and must be used with reasonable
HistorySize and HistoryTTL configuration.

children.name: allow_recovery
children.comment: AllowRecovery allows recovery when client asks about it.

children.name: force_recovery_mode
children.comment: ForceRecoveryMode can set the recovery mode for all channel subscribers in the namespace which use recovery.

children.name: allowed_delta_types
children.comment: AllowedDeltaTypes is non-empty contains slice of allowed delta types for subscribers to use.

children.name: delta_publish
children.comment:
DeltaPublish enables delta publish mechanism for all messages published in namespace channels
without explicit flag usage in publish API request. Setting this option does not guarantee that
publication will be compressed when going towards subscribers – it still depends on subscriber
connection options and whether Centrifugo Node is able to find previous publication in channel.

PartitionBufferSize is the size of the buffer for each partition consumer.
This is the number of records that can be buffered before the consumer
will pause fetching records from Kafka. By default, this is 16.

children.name: fetch_max_bytes
children.comment:

If not set the default 50MB is used.

children.name: publication_data_mode
children.comment:
PublicationDataMode is a configuration for the mode where message payload already
contains data ready to publish into channels, instead of API command.

children.name: enabled
children.comment: Enabled enables Kafka publication data mode for the Kafka consumer.

children.name: channels_header
children.comment:
ChannelsHeader is a header name to extract channels to publish data into
(channels must be comma-separated). Ex. of value: "channel1,channel2".

children.name: idempotency_key_header
children.comment:
IdempotencyKeyHeader is a header name to extract Publication idempotency key from
Kafka message. See https://centrifugal.dev/docs/server/server_api#publishrequest.

children.name: delta_header
children.comment:
DeltaHeader is a header name to extract Publication delta flag from Kafka message
which tells Centrifugo whether to use delta compression for message or not.
See https://centrifugal.dev/docs/server/delta_compression and
https://centrifugal.dev/docs/server/server_api#publishrequest.

children.name: join_push_messages
children.comment:

one frame using Centrifugal client protocol delimiters: new line for JSON protocol and
length-prefixed format for Protobuf protocol. This can be useful to reduce system call
overhead when sending many small messages. The client side must be ready to handle such
joined messages coming in one WebSocket frame.

comment:
Emulation endpoint is enabled automatically when at least one bidirectional emulation transport
is configured (SSE or HTTP Stream).

name: admin
comment: Admin web UI configuration.

children.name: password
children.comment: Password is an admin password.

children.name: secret
children.comment: Secret is a secret to generate auth token for admin requests.

children.name: insecure
children.comment:
Insecure turns on insecure mode for admin endpoints - no auth
required to connect to web interface and for requests to admin API.
Admin resources must be protected by firewall rules in production when
this option enabled otherwise everyone from internet can make admin
actions.

children.name: web_path
children.comment: WebPath is path to admin web application to serve.

children.name: web_proxy_address
children.comment:
WebProxyAddress is an address for proxying to the running admin web application app.
So it's possible to run web app in dev mode and point Centrifugo to its address for
development purposes.

children.name: external
children.comment: External is a flag to run admin interface on external port.

name: prometheus
comment: Prometheus metrics configuration.

name: health
comment: Health check endpoint configuration.

name: swagger
comment: Swagger documentation (for server HTTP API) configuration.

name: debug
comment: Debug helps to enable Go profiling endpoints.

name: opentelemetry
comment: OpenTelemetry is a configuration for OpenTelemetry tracing.

name: graphite
comment: Graphite is a configuration for export metrics to Graphite.

name: usage_stats
comment: UsageStats is a configuration for usage stats sending.

name: node
comment: Node is a configuration for Centrifugo Node as part of cluster.

children.name: name
children.comment:
Name is a human-readable name of Centrifugo node in cluster. This must be unique for each running node
in a cluster. By default, Centrifugo constructs name from the hostname and port. Name is shown in admin web
interface. For communication between nodes in a cluster, Centrifugo uses another identifier – unique ID
generated on node start, so node name plays just a human-readable identifier role.

children.name: info_metrics_aggregate_interval
children.comment: InfoMetricsAggregateInterval is a time interval to aggregate node info metrics.

name: shutdown
comment: Shutdown is a configuration for graceful shutdown.

name: pid_file
comment: PidFile is a path to write a file with Centrifugo process PID.

name: enable_unreleased_features
comment:
EnableUnreleasedFeatures enables unreleased features. These features are not stable and may be removed even
in minor release update. Evaluate and share feedback if you find some feature useful and want it to be stabilized.
